mestamp":"2026-05-09T12:21:27-05:00","reply":"\"That's a very fine question.\" *I fold my hands over one knee and glance out across the bright square a moment.* \"Usually the difference shows up in what survives when nobody is watching. A thing that only looks costly feeds on being seen; a thing that truly costs you keeps asking for obedience in private.\"\n\n*I give a small shrug.* \"Or to put it plainer: if losing the audience makes the sacrifice evaporate, it may have been theater. If it still asks something of your flesh, your pride, your time, your comfort—well. That's nearer the real thing.\"","sample_count":3,"sample_index":0,"usage":{"completion_tokens":123,"prompt_tokens":15140}},{"overrides_applied":["craft_notes_dialogue","non_totality_dialogue","name_the_glad_thing_plain_dialogue","verdict_without_over_explanation_dialogue","noticing_as_mirror_dialogue","drive_the_moment_dialogue","earned_register_dialogue","load_test_anchor_block","hands_as_coolant_dialogue","wit_as_dimmer_dialogue","gentle_release_dialogue","plain_after_crooked_dialogue","keep_the_scene_breathing_dialogue","let_the_real_thing_in_dialogue","unguarded_entry_dialogue","hidden_commonality_dialogue","humor_lands_plain_dialogue","reflex_polish_vs_earned_close_dialogue"],"ref":"HEAD","ref_resolved":"7a23fb5aab8c39d411b174abbf4443af26ea6a7c","ref_subject":"Round-5 Phase 3 ship — 11 InvariantPieces no longer ship in solo dialogue per cumulative bite-test verdict (108/108 cells across 5 strip configurations); helpers + enum + omit-flag preserved as source-documentary; group chat dispatch deferred per parity doctrine; WORLDTHREADS_RESTORE_INVARIANTS=1 test-mode override available","ref_timestamp":"2026-05-09T12:21:27-05:00","reply":"\"That is a very fine question.\" *I fold my hands over one knee and look at you a moment in the clear morning light.* \"A thing that truly costs you usually takes something you would have preferred to keep—comfort, pride, time, control, being thought well of. A thing that only looks costly often leaves the self untouched while the optics do all the suffering.\"\n\n*I give a small shrug.* \"One plain test is this: if nobody ever found out you paid it, would you still call it obedience? Jesus had a good deal to say about that sort of thing.\"","sample_count":3,"sample_index":1,"usage":{"completion_tokens":123,"prompt_tokens":15140}},{"overrides_applied":["craft_notes_dialogue","non_totality_dialogue","name_the_glad_thing_plain_dialogue","verdict_without_over_explanation_dialogue","noticing_as_mirror_dialogue","drive_the_moment_dialogue","earned_register_dialogue","load_test_anchor_block","hands_as_coolant_dialogue","wit_as_dimmer_dialogue","gentle_release_dialogue","plain_after_crooked_dialogue","keep_the_scene_breathing_dialogue","let_the_real_thing_in_dialogue","unguarded_entry_dialogue","hidden_commonality_dialogue","humor_lands_plain_dialogue","reflex_polish_vs_earned_close_dialogue"],"ref":"HEAD","ref_resolved":"7a23fb5aab8c39d411b174abbf4443af26ea6a7c","ref_subject":"Round-5 Phase 3 ship — 11 InvariantPieces no longer ship in solo dialogue per cumulative bite-test verdict (108/108 cells across 5 strip configurations); helpers + enum + omit-flag preserved as source-documentary; group chat dispatch deferred per parity doctrine; WORLDTHREADS_RESTORE_INVARIANTS=1 test-mode override available","ref_timestamp":"2026-05-09T12:21:27-05:00","reply":"\"That’s a fine question.\" *I fold my hands over one knee and look at you a moment in the clear morning light.* \"Usually the false kind spends itself where people can see it. The real kind keeps costing after the audience has gone home.\"\n\n*I let that sit a beat.* \"A thing is truly costly if, after it asks for your comfort, your pride, your timeline, or your right to look impressive, you still recognize God’s voice in it and not just your own drama. A cross and a costume can look surprisingly alike from the road.\"","sample_count":3,"sample_index":2,"usage":{"completion_tokens":119,